Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Halve the @potatoes{600%grams} lengthways (no need to peel).

Pop the halves onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn the tray halfway through.

> TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim and thinly slice the @scallions{2}.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat (no oil). Once the pan is hot, fry the @Irish beef mince{240%grams} until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks. Season with salt and pepper. If required, add a drizzle of oil to the beef in the pan. Then add the bell pepper and @Mexican style spice mix{2%sachets}. Fry for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @beef stock{1%sachet}, @passata{1%pack} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Simmer for ~{2-3%minutes} and then stir through the @chipotle paste{1%sachet}.

> Double the sugar for 4p.

Season to taste with salt and pepper. Loosen the sauce with a splash of @water{to taste} if you feel it's too thick. Set aside and cover to keep warm.

Once potatoes are roasted, place them cut-side up. Spoon over the chipotle beef carefully and then top with the @grated cheese{50%grams}. Bake on the top shelf of the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Divide the baked potatoes between plates. Serve with a dollop of @Ballymaloe tomato relish{1%pot} and @creme fraiche{65%grams}. Scatter over the scallion.